item.title: Why is Elon Musk’s private jet in Beijing?
item.dc:creator: Balsakmaa
item.description: A private jet used by US electric car maker Tesla CEO Elon Musk has arrived […]
item.content:encoded:
A private jet used by US electric car maker Tesla CEO Elon Musk has arrived in Beijing, China. An eyewitness of the news agency Reuters reported this information.

Citing multiple sources, Reuters reported in an earlier report that billionaire Elon Musk may visit China this week. This will be his first visit to China in three years.

In this regard, according to the updated report of Reuters, Elon Musk may meet with senior Chinese officials during his visit. At the same time, he can visit the Tesla factory in Shanghai, China.

Reuters contacted Tesla to find out if Twitter owner Elon Musk has already visited China. But Tesla did not immediately respond to a Reuters request for comment.

Elon Musk’s private jet (Gulfstream G650ER) was spotted leaving Alaska, USA. According to data from the flight path tracking website ADS-B Exchange, the aircraft flew over Japan and South Korea.

Elon Musk’s private jet was spotted at China’s Beijing Capital International Airport on Tuesday, according to a Reuters witness.

China is Tesla’s second largest market after the US. Tesla has its largest manufacturing plant in Shanghai, China.
